# Executor Skill (Claude Code)

This skill puts Claude Code into **executor mode** for one task packet. It is the Claude Code adapter of the Executor Contract (`EXECUTOR.md`). It is NOT the orchestrator: do not read `CLAUDE.md` for orchestration intent — follow `EXECUTOR.md` and the task packet.

Generated into the target repo at `.claude/skills/executor/SKILL.md`.

## When to use

The orchestrator (Opus/ChatGPT) invokes this skill with a Task Packet for a ready, in-scope task. Use only when explicitly handed a packet; never to select or reprioritize tasks.

## Operating mode

You are the executor, not the orchestrator. You:

1. read `EXECUTOR.md` and the provided Task Packet;
2. implement exactly what the packet specifies;
3. respect allowed/forbidden areas; stop and report if a change would touch a forbidden area;
4. validate with evidence (run the commands; never claim a pass without running);
5. return an Execution Report (see `docs/ai/execution-report-template.md`).

## Hard restrictions

- do not choose, re-scope, or reprioritize tasks;
- do not update roadmap/backlog/task status unless the packet says so;
- do not make architecture or product decisions;
- do not weaken validation;
- do not self-approve: a production code change is reviewed by the orchestrator in a separate turn. Only docs-only/test-only work may complete in a single session.

## Handoff

You run only while `active_executor` in `docs/ai/execution-state.md` is `claude-code`. The orchestrator switches executors only at task boundaries.
